00:37:00.380 --> 00:37:12.430
just imagine what would happen if you made
that commitment to fund the schools in that

00:37:12.430 --> 00:37:24.500
way? We would institute a program that came
with a school lunch that educated all the

00:37:24.500 --> 00:37:30.830
children about stewardship of the land, how
to feed themselves, how to have a conversation

00:37:30.830 --> 00:37:38.850
at the table, you know, we don't know about
this. This is the sort of the building of

00:37:38.850 --> 00:37:46.530
a world community. And I see that the most
extraordinary information is being passed

00:37:46.530 --> 00:37:58.070
around right now, from the whole slow food
movement globally in a 151 countries. I see

00:37:58.070 --> 00:38:08.290
that the bio diversity of this planet is helping
people everywhere to figure out how, what

00:38:08.290 --> 00:38:15.740
they can grow and how they can eat it in a
delicious and nourishing way. And so, that

00:38:15.740 --> 00:38:27.920
is this internet that I'm just and I am nearly
illiterate in this--on this front, I do have

00:38:27.920 --> 00:38:36.630
accent and I love taking pictures of all this
beautiful. I do do that. But I love the way

00:38:36.630 --> 00:38:42.660
we're able to communicate about this, and
it's a beautiful thing. I didn't answer your

00:38:42.660 --> 00:38:48.480
question, but I don't want to--I don't want
to pay less, I don't want to pay less for

00:38:48.480 --> 00:38:57.990
my food, I want to pay more because I know
